    "department": "Product",
    "description": "OVERVIEW\n\nAs a Product Designer at Phia, you’ll help design user experiences across core product surfaces. You’ll work closely with Product, Engineering, and other designers to turn ideas into clear, usable designs that ship. This role offers hands-on exposure to the full product design process, from early concepts to production, in a fast-moving environment. You’ll learn by shipping real work, iterating quickly, and contributing to products used by a growing audience.\n\n\nABOUT PHIA\n\nPhia has raised $43M from Notable Capital, Khosla Ventures, and Kleiner Perkins to build the AI alignment layer for commerce. In under a year, Phia’s consumer shopping agent has surpassed one million users and partnered with 6,200+ retail brands, representing billions in annual gross merchandise volume. Each month, Phia drives millions of dollars in sales for brands and has achieved 11× revenue growth since launch.\n\nIn an era where AI vertical agents are reshaping every industry, commerce is on the verge of a complete transformation. Phia is reinventing shopping from a fragmented, impersonal experience into one that feels intelligent, trusted, and built around each user’s intent. This foundation of trust is our wedge to become the end-to-end shopping destination for the next generation of buyers.\n\nPhia is a lean, high-ownership team building at startup speed. If you want to ship at high velocity and solve complex problems in consumer AI and commerce, this is the place to do it.\n\n\nWHAT YOU OWN\n\n - Support the design of user flows, interfaces, and interactions across the product\n\n - Create wireframes, high-fidelity designs, and basic prototypes\n\n - Partner with product managers and engineers to bring designs to life\n\n - Iterate on designs based on feedback, user insights, and product goals\n\n - Help maintain and apply design systems and patterns\n\n - Learn and follow best practices for usability and accessibility\n\n\nQUALIFICATIONS\n\n - 1+ years of experience or equivalent coursework in product, UX, or interaction design\n\n - Strong foundation in user-centered design principles and visual design basics\n\n - Familiarity with design tools such as Figma or similar\n\n - Interest in building consumer products and learning end-to-end design workflows\n\n - Ability to take feedback, learn quickly, and iterate in a fast-paced environment\n\n - Clear communication skills and strong attention to detail",
